{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:47:19.331270+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive summary.\n\n---\n\n## How to Run, Build, and Preview This React Admin App\n\n### Overview\n\nThis is a **Vite + React + TypeScript + Material UI (MUI)** admin dashboard. It uses **Yarn** as its package manager and supports three environment modes: **local**, **staging**, and **production**. Environment-specific configuration lives in the `envs/` directory (`.env.local`, `.env.stg`, `.env.prod`).\n\n---\n\n### 1. Initial Setup\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\nyarn install\n\n# Or, using the Taskfile helper (installs global tools + copies .env.local + runs yarn install)\ntask init\n```\n\nThe `task init` command copies `envs/.env.local` → `.env` and installs global tools like `commitizen`, `conventional-changelog-cli`, and `standard-version`.\n\n> **Note:** Vite resolves `.env` first, and falls back to `envs/.env.<NODE_ENV>` if no `.env` exists at the root.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Running Locally (Development Server)\n\n| Command | Environment | What it does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `yarn dev` | **Local** | Sets `NODE_ENV=local`, starts Vite dev server on port **10086** with `--host` (accessible on LAN) |\n| `yarn dev:stg` | **Staging** | Sets `NODE_ENV=stg`, starts Vite dev server on port **10086** |\n\n- Both commands spin up the Vite dev server with hot module replacement (HMR).\n- The local environment uses the mock API at `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd`.\n- The staging environment uses `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Building for Production / Staging\n\n| Command | Mode | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | `prod` | Builds with Vite mode `prod` (loads `envs/.env.prod`) |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `test` | Builds with Vite mode `test` (loads the staging env) |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `production` | Builds with Vite mode `production` |\n\nAll build commands output to the `dist/` directory.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Previewing a Build\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\n\nThis runs `vite preview --host`, which serves the contents of the `dist/` folder locally so you can verify the production build before deploying.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Deploying\n\n- **GitHub Pages:** `yarn deploy` (uses `gh-pages -d dist`)\n- **Netlify:** A `netlify.toml` is included with a catch-all SPA redirect (`/* → /`, status 200).\n- **Docker / Nginx:** A multi-stage `Dockerfile` is provided:\n  1. Builds the app inside `node:lts-alpine`.\n  2. Copies `dist/` and `nginx.conf` into an `nginx:alpine` image.\n  3. Serves on **port 80** with SPA fallback (`try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html`).\n\n```bash\n# Build and run the Docker image\ndocker build -t vite-react-admin .\ndocker run -p 80:80 vite-react-admin\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Other Useful Commands\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `yarn lint` | Run ESLint across `.jsx`, `.js`, `.ts`, `.tsx` files |\n| `yarn fix` | Auto-fix lint issues |\n| `task changelog` | Generate a changelog from conventional commits |\n| `task release` | Bump version, generate changelog, commit, and push |\n| `task commit` | Stage all, commit via Commitizen, and push |\n\n---\n\n### Environment Variables Summary\n\n| Variable | Local | Staging | Production |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `NODE_ENV` | `local` | `stg` | `prod` |\n| `VITE_PORT` | `10086` | `10086` | *(empty)* |\n| `VITE_APP_BASE_API` | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n| `VITE_BASE_URL` | `./` | `./` | `./` |\n| `VITE_OUTPUT_DIR` | `dist` | `dist` | `dist` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1497, "prompt_tokens": 8670, "total_tokens": 10167, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 489, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8128, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0015674208, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002650308, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00130239}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962413-MssOCXcrx9uuOT5xKXdG", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a1-cb71-7240-a4b7-c2ce5cf624bd-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8670, "output_tokens": 1497, "total_tokens": 10167, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8128}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 489}}}}]}}}
